{"word":"G1658 - ἐλεύθερος - eleútheros - el-yoo'-ther-os - Free","slug":"G1658","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἐλεύθερος</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>eleútheros"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>el-yoo'-ther-os"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Free"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B5;&#x0313;&#x03BB;&#x03B5;&#x03C5;&#x0301;&#x03B8;&#x03B5;&#x03C1;&#x03BF;&#x03C2; - eleutheros</b> - <i>el-yoo'-ther-os</i><p/>Probably from the alternate of <a href=\"#/G2064\">G2064</a>; <i>unrestrained</i> (to <i>go</i> at pleasure), that is, (as a citizen) <i>not a slave</i> (whether <i>freeborn</i> or <i>manumitted</i>), or (generally) <i>exempt</i> (from obligation or liability): - free (man, woman), at liberty."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1657\">G1657</a>, <a href=\"#/G1659\">G1659</a>, <a href=\"#/G558\">G558</a>"}]}